    {
      "id": "z4V_AydKrnF211wD0N366",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 184.01487088932774,
      "y": 1393.1012726979832,
      "width": 513.088623046875,
      "height": 6060,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#343a40",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "as",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 451105049,
      "version": 403,
      "versionNonce": 1076579927,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [
        {
          "id": "2rnET6VMd63IsRUAMK9pu",
          "type": "arrow"
        }
      ],
      "updated": 1773806344397,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Chapter 1: Head Office — The Master Brain\n\n   Port ko main tower मा बस्ने team धेरै smart थियो.\n   यो team आफैं cargo bok्दैन थियो,  \n   तर decide, manage, monitor गर्थ्यो.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nयसलाई technical language मा भनिन्छ: Control Plane\n\n\n\nControl Plane\n\n   यस control plane भित्र 4 जना very important officers थिए:\n\n           kube-apiserver\n\n           etcd\n\n           kube-scheduler\n\n           kube-controller-manager\n\nअब हेर, यी को को हुन्:\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nkube-apiserver = Front Desk / Radio Office\n\n\n      Port मा एउटा main office थियो जहाँ \n        सबै calls, orders, approvals आउँथे.\n\n     Customer ले भन्नु पर्‍यो:\n\n        “मलाई 3 वटा nginx containers चाहिन्छ”\n\n     Admin ले भन्नु पर्‍यो:\n\n         “Deploy this app”\n\n\n\n     सबै request यही office मा आउँथ्यो.\n\n\n\n\n\nTechnical रूपमा:\n\n     kubectl talks to kube-apiserver\n\n     all cluster communication mostly \n       passes via API server\n\n\n\n\n\n     Analogy:\n\n          kube-apiserver = port ko front desk \n                           + radio communication room\n\n\n\n\n     जसरी airport मा control tower बिना flight manage हुँदैन, \n     त्यसरी API server बिना cluster communicate हुँदैन.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\netcd = Secret Record Room / Master Register\n\n     Head office भित्र एउटा secure room थियो.\n     \n     त्यो room मा सबै official documents, manifests, \n         cargo lists, ship assignments राखिन्थ्यो.\n\n\n\n\n     त्यो room को नाम थियो:\n\n     etcd\n\n        यसले याद राख्थ्यो:\n\n          कुन ship active छ\n\n          कुन cargo कहाँ जानुपर्छ\n\n          कुन app को कति replicas चाहिन्छ\n\n          service कहाँ point गर्छ\n\n          secret key के हो\n\n          cluster ko state के छ\n\n\n\n\nAnalogy:\n\n     etcd = company ko master diary / cargo registry \n               / official database\n\n\n\n\n\n\n     Nepali मा भन्नुपर्दा:\n\n          “यो cluster ko memory ho.”\n\n          यदि etcd हरायो भने, headquarters लाई धेरै कुरा बिर्सिन्छ.\n\n\n\n\n\n\nkube-scheduler = Cargo Placement Manager\n\n     अब customer ko order आयो:\n\n          “3 वटा web pods चाहियो”\n\n     अब question आयो:\n\n          “यी pods कुन ship मा पठाउने?”\n\n\n     यो decide गर्ने officer थियो:\n\n\n\n\n     kube-scheduler\n\n          यसले check गर्थ्यो:\n\n               कुन worker node मा enough CPU छ\n\n               memory पुग्छ कि पुग्दैन\n\n               special taint छ कि छैन\n\n               affinity rules मिल्छ कि मिल्दैन\n\n               busy छ कि खाली\n\n\n\n\n    Analogy:\n    \n         जसरी port manager ले भन्छ:\n    \n         “यो refrigerated cargo Ship B मा जान्छ”\n         “यो heavy cargo Ship C मा हाल”\n         “Ship A already full छ”\n\n\n\n\n        त्यसरी scheduler ले decide गर्छ:\n        \n             “This pod goes to node-2”\n\n\n\n\nImportant:\n\n    Scheduler runs nothing.\n    It only selects where to run.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nkube-controller-manager = Operations Inspector\n\n\n\n    अब अर्को officer थियो, अलि strict type ko.\n\n        यसको काम थियो:\n\n            “Plan अनुसार सबै कुरा भइरहेको छ कि छैन?”\n\n\n\n\n    Suppose company ले plan बनायो:\n\n            3 pods running हुनुपर्छ\n\n        तर actual मा 2 मात्रै रहेछ.\n\n    तुरुन्त यो officer ले भन्यो:\n\n            “ए, एउटा missing छ, replacement पठाऊ!”\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n        यो officer technical रूपमा:\n\n                kube-controller-manager\n\n        यसले reconcile गर्छ:\n        \n            desired state\n            \n            actual state\n\n\n\n\n\n        Analogy:\n        \n            Operations supervisor / quality inspector \n            / compliance manager\n        \n        \n        \n        Nepali feeling मा:\n        \n            “जति order गरेको थियो, उति पुगेको छ कि \n            छैन भनेर check गर्ने dai.”",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Chapter 1: Head Office — The Master Brain\n\n   Port ko main tower मा बस्ने team धेरै smart थियो.\n   यो team आफैं cargo bok्दैन थियो,  \n   तर decide, manage, monitor गर्थ्यो.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nयसलाई technical language मा भनिन्छ: Control Plane\n\n\n\nControl Plane\n\n   यस control plane भित्र 4 जना very important officers थिए:\n\n           kube-apiserver\n\n           etcd\n\n           kube-scheduler\n\n           kube-controller-manager\n\nअब हेर, यी को को हुन्:\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nkube-apiserver = Front Desk / Radio Office\n\n\n      Port मा एउटा main office थियो जहाँ \n        सबै calls, orders, approvals आउँथे.\n\n     Customer ले भन्नु पर्‍यो:\n\n        “मलाई 3 वटा nginx containers चाहिन्छ”\n\n     Admin ले भन्नु पर्‍यो:\n\n         “Deploy this app”\n\n\n\n     सबै request यही office मा आउँथ्यो.\n\n\n\n\n\nTechnical रूपमा:\n\n     kubectl talks to kube-apiserver\n\n     all cluster communication mostly \n       passes via API server\n\n\n\n\n\n     Analogy:\n\n          kube-apiserver = port ko front desk \n                           + radio communication room\n\n\n\n\n     जसरी airport मा control tower बिना flight manage हुँदैन, \n     त्यसरी API server बिना cluster communicate हुँदैन.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\netcd = Secret Record Room / Master Register\n\n     Head office भित्र एउटा secure room थियो.\n     \n     त्यो room मा सबै official documents, manifests, \n         cargo lists, ship assignments राखिन्थ्यो.\n\n\n\n\n     त्यो room को नाम थियो:\n\n     etcd\n\n        यसले याद राख्थ्यो:\n\n          कुन ship active छ\n\n          कुन cargo कहाँ जानुपर्छ\n\n          कुन app को कति replicas चाहिन्छ\n\n          service कहाँ point गर्छ\n\n          secret key के हो\n\n          cluster ko state के छ\n\n\n\n\nAnalogy:\n\n     etcd = company ko master diary / cargo registry \n               / official database\n\n\n\n\n\n\n     Nepali मा भन्नुपर्दा:\n\n          “यो cluster ko memory ho.”\n\n          यदि etcd हरायो भने, headquarters लाई धेरै कुरा बिर्सिन्छ.\n\n\n\n\n\n\nkube-scheduler = Cargo Placement Manager\n\n     अब customer ko order आयो:\n\n          “3 वटा web pods चाहियो”\n\n     अब question आयो:\n\n          “यी pods कुन ship मा पठाउने?”\n\n\n     यो decide गर्ने officer थियो:\n\n\n\n\n     kube-scheduler\n\n          यसले check गर्थ्यो:\n\n               कुन worker node मा enough CPU छ\n\n               memory पुग्छ कि पुग्दैन\n\n               special taint छ कि छैन\n\n               affinity rules मिल्छ कि मिल्दैन\n\n               busy छ कि खाली\n\n\n\n\n    Analogy:\n    \n         जसरी port manager ले भन्छ:\n    \n         “यो refrigerated cargo Ship B मा जान्छ”\n         “यो heavy cargo Ship C मा हाल”\n         “Ship A already full छ”\n\n\n\n\n        त्यसरी scheduler ले decide गर्छ:\n        \n             “This pod goes to node-2”\n\n\n\n\nImportant:\n\n    Scheduler runs nothing.\n    It only selects where to run.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nkube-controller-manager = Operations Inspector\n\n\n\n    अब अर्को officer थियो, अलि strict type ko.\n\n        यसको काम थियो:\n\n            “Plan अनुसार सबै कुरा भइरहेको छ कि छैन?”\n\n\n\n\n    Suppose company ले plan बनायो:\n\n            3 pods running हुनुपर्छ\n\n        तर actual मा 2 मात्रै रहेछ.\n\n    तुरुन्त यो officer ले भन्यो:\n\n            “ए, एउटा missing छ, replacement पठाऊ!”\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n        यो officer technical रूपमा:\n\n                kube-controller-manager\n\n        यसले reconcile गर्छ:\n        \n            desired state\n            \n            actual state\n\n\n\n\n\n        Analogy:\n        \n            Operations supervisor / quality inspector \n            / compliance manager\n        \n        \n        \n        Nepali feeling मा:\n        \n            “जति order गरेको थियो, उति पुगेको छ कि \n            छैन भनेर check गर्ने dai.”",
