    {
      "id": "zbnsFedoe2us-2LOVNXF_",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 253.8253963316187,
      "y": 8219.250634349868,
      "width": 515.8090209960938,
      "height": 4840,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#343a40",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0Q",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 307884599,
      "version": 193,
      "versionNonce": 42492887,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1773806344397,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Chapter 2: Worker Ships — Where Actual Work Happens\n\n\n\n    अब head office ले निर्णय गर्‍यो, तर \n    actual cargo बोक्ने को?\n    \n    त्यो हुन्:\n    \n        Worker Nodes\n        \n            यी हुन् real ships.\n            \n            यहाँ नै actual applications run हुन्छन्.\n\n\n\n\nTechnical:\n\n    Worker nodes run:\n    \n        Pods\n        \n        kubelet\n        \n        kube-proxy\n        \n        container runtime\n\n\n\n\n\n\nAnalogy:\n\n    Worker nodes = cargo ships in the sea\n\n\n\n\n\nPod = Cargo Package Unit\n\n     अब एउटा ship मा directly scattered सामान हालिँदैन.\n     Saman organized package मा जान्छ.\n        \n        Kubernetes मा त्यो smallest deployable package हो:\n        \n        \n\n\n        Pod\n        \n            A pod may contain:\n        \n                one container\n                \n                or multiple tightly-coupled containers\n        \n        \n\n\n    Analogy:\n        \n        Pod = cargo section / shipment packet\n        \n\n        Sometimes एउटा pod = एउटा container box\n        कहिलेकाहीँ pod = एउटा main box + side helper box\n        \n\n        जस्तै:\n        \n            main app container\n            \n            sidecar logging container\n        \n        \n\n\n\n\n\nContainer = The Actual Cargo Box\n\n    यो नै वास्तविक सामान हो.\n\n        Example:\n\n            nginx container\n            \n            redis container\n            \n            python app container\n\n\n\n    Analogy:\n\n        Container = sealed cargo box\n\n\n\n\n    Pod भनेको box राख्ने shipment unit हो,\n\n    container भनेको actual box हो.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nkubelet = Ship Captain\n\n\n    हरेक ship मा एउटा responsible captain हुन्थ्यो.\n\n        Head office बाट message आयो:\n\n            “Ship-2, run these 3 pods”\n\n\n\n\nत्यो order सुन्ने, implement गर्ने, status send गर्ने officer:\n\nkubelet\n\n        Technical:\n        \n            node agent\n            \n            ensures pods are running\n            \n            talks with API server\n            \n            reports health/status\n    \n\n\n\nAnalogy:\n\n    kubelet = ship ko captain / onboard officer\n\n    \n        Nepali मा:\n    \n            “Master ले जे काम दिन्छ, त्यो worker node \n                मा गराउने captain”\n    \n\n\n\n\n\nContainer Runtime = Crane + Engine Room\n\n\n    अब कप्तानले भनेपछि cargo आफैं load हुँदैन.\n    त्यसका लागि machinery चाहिन्छ.\n\n\n    यो हो:\n    \n        Container Runtime\n        \n            Examples:\n                \n                containerd\n                \n                CRI-O\n    \n    \n            Older diagram मा Docker देखिन सक्छ.\n    \n    \n\n\n    Analogy:\n    \n        container runtime = crane + loading machine \n                                  + engine room\n        \n\n\n\n\n\n        Scheduler ले decide गर्छ\n        kubelet ले आदेश दिन्छ\n        runtime ले actual container start गर्छ\n        \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nkube-proxy = Route Police / Traffic Controller\n\n\n\n  अब ships मा cargo पुगेपछि ग्राहकको request सही ठाउँमा जानुपर्‍यो.\n    \n        यो काम गर्छ:\n    \n        kube-proxy\n   \n\n\n\n Technical:\n    \n    It handles node-level networking rules so\n     traffic reaches the right pods.\n    \n\n\n    \n    Analogy:\n    \n        जसरी harbor traffic police ले route मिलाउँछ:\n        \n            यो truck dock 4 मा जा\n            \n            यो request warehouse B मा जा\n            \n            यो customer service लाई जा\n        \n        त्यसरी kube-proxy ले service traffic सही pod \n          सम्म पुर्‍याउँछ.",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Chapter 2: Worker Ships — Where Actual Work Happens\n\n\n\n    अब head office ले निर्णय गर्‍यो, तर \n    actual cargo बोक्ने को?\n    \n    त्यो हुन्:\n    \n        Worker Nodes\n        \n            यी हुन् real ships.\n            \n            यहाँ नै actual applications run हुन्छन्.\n\n\n\n\nTechnical:\n\n    Worker nodes run:\n    \n        Pods\n        \n        kubelet\n        \n        kube-proxy\n        \n        container runtime\n\n\n\n\n\n\nAnalogy:\n\n    Worker nodes = cargo ships in the sea\n\n\n\n\n\nPod = Cargo Package Unit\n\n     अब एउटा ship मा directly scattered सामान हालिँदैन.\n     Saman organized package मा जान्छ.\n        \n        Kubernetes मा त्यो smallest deployable package हो:\n        \n        \n\n\n        Pod\n        \n            A pod may contain:\n        \n                one container\n                \n                or multiple tightly-coupled containers\n        \n        \n\n\n    Analogy:\n        \n        Pod = cargo section / shipment packet\n        \n\n        Sometimes एउटा pod = एउटा container box\n        कहिलेकाहीँ pod = एउटा main box + side helper box\n        \n\n        जस्तै:\n        \n            main app container\n            \n            sidecar logging container\n        \n        \n\n\n\n\n\nContainer = The Actual Cargo Box\n\n    यो नै वास्तविक सामान हो.\n\n        Example:\n\n            nginx container\n            \n            redis container\n            \n            python app container\n\n\n\n    Analogy:\n\n        Container = sealed cargo box\n\n\n\n\n    Pod भनेको box राख्ने shipment unit हो,\n\n    container भनेको actual box हो.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nkubelet = Ship Captain\n\n\n    हरेक ship मा एउटा responsible captain हुन्थ्यो.\n\n        Head office बाट message आयो:\n\n            “Ship-2, run these 3 pods”\n\n\n\n\nत्यो order सुन्ने, implement गर्ने, status send गर्ने officer:\n\nkubelet\n\n        Technical:\n        \n            node agent\n            \n            ensures pods are running\n            \n            talks with API server\n            \n            reports health/status\n    \n\n\n\nAnalogy:\n\n    kubelet = ship ko captain / onboard officer\n\n    \n        Nepali मा:\n    \n            “Master ले जे काम दिन्छ, त्यो worker node \n                मा गराउने captain”\n    \n\n\n\n\n\nContainer Runtime = Crane + Engine Room\n\n\n    अब कप्तानले भनेपछि cargo आफैं load हुँदैन.\n    त्यसका लागि machinery चाहिन्छ.\n\n\n    यो हो:\n    \n        Container Runtime\n        \n            Examples:\n                \n                containerd\n                \n                CRI-O\n    \n    \n            Older diagram मा Docker देखिन सक्छ.\n    \n    \n\n\n    Analogy:\n    \n        container runtime = crane + loading machine \n                                  + engine room\n        \n\n\n\n\n\n        Scheduler ले decide गर्छ\n        kubelet ले आदेश दिन्छ\n        runtime ले actual container start गर्छ\n        \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nkube-proxy = Route Police / Traffic Controller\n\n\n\n  अब ships मा cargo पुगेपछि ग्राहकको request सही ठाउँमा जानुपर्‍यो.\n    \n        यो काम गर्छ:\n    \n        kube-proxy\n   \n\n\n\n Technical:\n    \n    It handles node-level networking rules so\n     traffic reaches the right pods.\n    \n\n\n    \n    Analogy:\n    \n        जसरी harbor traffic police ले route मिलाउँछ:\n        \n            यो truck dock 4 मा जा\n            \n            यो request warehouse B मा जा\n            \n            यो customer service लाई जा\n        \n        त्यसरी kube-proxy ले service traffic सही pod \n          सम्म पुर्‍याउँछ.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
