      "updated": 1773806344397,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "One Full Workflow Story\n\n\n\n\n    अब एउटै real scenario imagine गर:\n\n    Admin Luke port HQ मा आयो अनि भन्यो:\n\n\n        kubectl apply -f web.yaml\n\n\n\n\nWhat happens?\n        \n        Step 1: API Server\n        \n            यो request kube-apiserver मा पुग्छ\n            जस्तै front desk मा form बुझायो\n        \n        \n        \n        Step 2: etcd\n        \n            यो desired state etcd मा save हुन्छ\n            जस्तै record room मा official entry भयो\n           \n        \n         \n        Step 3: Controller notices\n        \n            Controller ले बुझ्छ:\n            \n                “New Deployment चाहिएको रहेछ”\n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        Step 4: Scheduler decides\n        \n          Scheduler ले भन्यो:\n            \n            “Pod-1 ship A मा”\n            “Pod-2 ship B मा”\n            “Pod-3 ship B मा”\n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        Step 5: Kubelet acts\n        \n            हरेक ship ko captain (kubelet) ले \n            order receive गर्छ\n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        Step 6: Runtime loads cargo\n        \n            container runtime ले actual containers \n            start गर्छ\n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        Step 7: Service exposes app\n        \n                Customer लाई stable access दिन \n                Service create हुन्छ\n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        Step 8: Kube-proxy routes traffic\n        \n            Traffic सही pod सम्म पुग्छ\n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        Step 9: Controller keeps watching\n        \n            एक pod crash भयो भने \n            controller + replicaset \n        \n            ले replacement launch गर्छ",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "One Full Workflow Story\n\n\n\n\n    अब एउटै real scenario imagine गर:\n\n    Admin Luke port HQ मा आयो अनि भन्यो:\n\n\n        kubectl apply -f web.yaml\n\n\n\n\nWhat happens?\n        \n        Step 1: API Server\n        \n            यो request kube-apiserver मा पुग्छ\n            जस्तै front desk मा form बुझायो\n        \n        \n        \n        Step 2: etcd\n        \n            यो desired state etcd मा save हुन्छ\n            जस्तै record room मा official entry भयो\n           \n        \n         \n        Step 3: Controller notices\n        \n            Controller ले बुझ्छ:\n            \n                “New Deployment चाहिएको रहेछ”\n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        Step 4: Scheduler decides\n        \n          Scheduler ले भन्यो:\n            \n            “Pod-1 ship A मा”\n            “Pod-2 ship B मा”\n            “Pod-3 ship B मा”\n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        Step 5: Kubelet acts\n        \n            हरेक ship ko captain (kubelet) ले \n            order receive गर्छ\n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        Step 6: Runtime loads cargo\n        \n            container runtime ले actual containers \n            start गर्छ\n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        Step 7: Service exposes app\n        \n                Customer लाई stable access दिन \n                Service create हुन्छ\n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        Step 8: Kube-proxy routes traffic\n        \n            Traffic सही pod सम्म पुग्छ\n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        Step 9: Controller keeps watching\n        \n            एक pod crash भयो भने \n            controller + replicaset \n        \n            ले replacement launch गर्छ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
