    {
      "id": "3C2ygWkbe5qjps2TFn8Qo",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 215.1999969482422,
      "y": 198.60000610351562,
      "width": 891,
      "height": 5250,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1y",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1906192537,
      "version": 40,
      "versionNonce": 1158759417,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1773806491559,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Scenario-Based Questions with Answers\n\n\nअब story को आधारमा questions गरौं.\n\n\n\nQ1. In this cargo story, who is the main front desk of the company?\nAnswer:\n\nkube-apiserver\n\nWhy:\n\nBecause all requests come first to the API server, just like all orders \ncome to the harbor office front desk.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nQ2. Which component is like the company’s memory or official record room?\nAnswer:\n\netcd\n\nWhy:\n\nIt stores cluster state, configuration, secrets, object data, and \ndesired state.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nQ3. Who decides which ship should carry a cargo package?\nAnswer:\n\nkube-scheduler\n\nWhy:\n\nThe scheduler chooses which worker node should run a pod.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nQ4. Ship captain ko role कसले गर्छ?\nAnswer:\n\nkubelet\n\nWhy:\n\nkubelet runs on each worker node and ensures assigned pods are running.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nQ5. Cargo box actual मा के हो?\nAnswer:\n\nContainer\n\nWhy:\n\nContainer is the packaged application.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nQ6. Cargo shipment unit, where one or more boxes can stay together, what is that?\nAnswer:\n\nPod\n\nWhy:\n\nPod is the smallest deployable unit and may contain one or more containers.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nQ7. Different cargo zones like dev, prod, staging are called what?\nAnswer:\n\nNamespaces\n\nWhy:\n\nNamespaces divide resources logically inside one cluster.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nQ8. Your access badge that decides cluster, user, and default \nnamespace is called what?\nAnswer:\n\nContext\n\nWhy:\n\nA context in kubeconfig stores cluster + user + namespace.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nQ9. Stable customer counter that always forwards traffic to the right \ncargo unit is called what?\nAnswer:\n\nService\n\nWhy:\n\nService gives stable network identity to changing pods.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nQ10. If one cargo package falls into the sea and the system automatically \ncreates another one, which Kubernetes idea is this?\nAnswer:\n\nSelf-healing / ReplicaSet / Controller reconciliation\n\nWhy:\n\nControllers maintain desired state and recreate missing pods.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nQ11. Open instruction sheet without password is called?\nAnswer:\n\nConfigMap\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nQ12. Locked secure locker with password/token is called?\nAnswer:\n\nSecret\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nQ13. Which component acts like traffic police for requests?\nAnswer:\n\nkube-proxy\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nQ14. Warehouse booking form in the story corresponds to what?\nAnswer:\n\nPersistentVolumeClaim (PVC)\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nQ15. The official shipping plan saying “keep 3 copies running” is what?\nAnswer:\n\nDeployment",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Scenario-Based Questions with Answers\n\n\nअब story को आधारमा questions गरौं.\n\n\n\nQ1. In this cargo story, who is the main front desk of the company?\nAnswer:\n\nkube-apiserver\n\nWhy:\n\nBecause all requests come first to the API server, just like all orders \ncome to the harbor office front desk.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nQ2. Which component is like the company’s memory or official record room?\nAnswer:\n\netcd\n\nWhy:\n\nIt stores cluster state, configuration, secrets, object data, and \ndesired state.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nQ3. Who decides which ship should carry a cargo package?\nAnswer:\n\nkube-scheduler\n\nWhy:\n\nThe scheduler chooses which worker node should run a pod.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nQ4. Ship captain ko role कसले गर्छ?\nAnswer:\n\nkubelet\n\nWhy:\n\nkubelet runs on each worker node and ensures assigned pods are running.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nQ5. Cargo box actual मा के हो?\nAnswer:\n\nContainer\n\nWhy:\n\nContainer is the packaged application.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nQ6. Cargo shipment unit, where one or more boxes can stay together, what is that?\nAnswer:\n\nPod\n\nWhy:\n\nPod is the smallest deployable unit and may contain one or more containers.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nQ7. Different cargo zones like dev, prod, staging are called what?\nAnswer:\n\nNamespaces\n\nWhy:\n\nNamespaces divide resources logically inside one cluster.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nQ8. Your access badge that decides cluster, user, and default \nnamespace is called what?\nAnswer:\n\nContext\n\nWhy:\n\nA context in kubeconfig stores cluster + user + namespace.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nQ9. Stable customer counter that always forwards traffic to the right \ncargo unit is called what?\nAnswer:\n\nService\n\nWhy:\n\nService gives stable network identity to changing pods.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nQ10. If one cargo package falls into the sea and the system automatically \ncreates another one, which Kubernetes idea is this?\nAnswer:\n\nSelf-healing / ReplicaSet / Controller reconciliation\n\nWhy:\n\nControllers maintain desired state and recreate missing pods.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nQ11. Open instruction sheet without password is called?\nAnswer:\n\nConfigMap\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nQ12. Locked secure locker with password/token is called?\nAnswer:\n\nSecret\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nQ13. Which component acts like traffic police for requests?\nAnswer:\n\nkube-proxy\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nQ14. Warehouse booking form in the story corresponds to what?\nAnswer:\n\nPersistentVolumeClaim (PVC)\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nQ15. The official shipping plan saying “keep 3 copies running” is what?\nAnswer:\n\nDeployment",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
